## Research Projects

### Microfluidic and Nanotechnology-Based Drug Delivery

![Microfluidic Research](assets/images/project-1.jpg)

This project focuses on the development of microfluidic platforms for controlled synthesis and characterization of nanocarriers for pharmaceutical and biomedical applications.

**Key areas:**

- Microfluidic formulation of liposomal systems  
- Nanocarrier characterization and optimization  
- Drug delivery and transdermal applications  
- Photostability and biological compatibility testing  

---

### Liposomal Formulations and Biomedical Applications

![Liposomal Formulations](assets/images/project-2.jpg)

This work investigates liposomal delivery systems for improving formulation stability, biological performance, and controlled release behavior.

**Key areas:**

- Liposome preparation and characterization  
- DLS, NTA, ATR-FTIR, UV–Vis, DSC, SEM, TEM, and confocal microscopy  
- Formulation stability and release behavior  
- Biomedical and cosmetic applications  

